COMMENT.COVAL_DESCRIPTION: On 11Mar2016 the patient presented respiratory infection (probably due to bronchoaspiration) that was treated with Amoxiciline+clavulanic acid 1g/8h.

SAE.AEDESC: patient presents fever since hospitalization in our stroke unit. Treatment with Amoxiciline-Clavulanic Acid is initiated and mantained during the following days until discharge. Patient was discharged on 16feb/16 to an other hospital where feber was persistent. Even antibiothics are mantained patient finally died on 1/march/16 becouse of infection.

SAE.SAEDIAG: atrial fibrillation mild congestive heart failure
SAE.AEDESC: On 7Mar2016 patient came to emergenchy room due to disnea (48h of evolution). An EKG shows atrial fibrillation with rapid ventricular response that was treated with digoxine (non effective). A chest X-Ray shows mild congestive heart failure. As patient was anticoagulated with acenocumarol and INR was correct, pharmacological cardioversion was performed with amiodarone bolus and continuous infusion. Patient remains hospitalized.
